    "Loop hunt round 5: false-positive guardian on D tiles + 600T floor budget (build 333). User: 'Scan the low floor, high turn playtests and squash more loops.' Two finds. (1) s=941 dwarf 2192T on F1 at FULL HP with D reachable, 0 loop_turns flagged. T404 trace: agent at (18,14), D adjacent at (17,14) west, neighbours read 'w': 'D' but inferred_guardian_dirs included 'w'. _suspected_guardian_coords_obs was flagging EVERY tile cardinal-adjacent to a discovered T as a guardian spawn -- including the D tile that happened to neighbour a T. Policy refused 'w' onto D, agent paced (18,14)-(19,16) for 1700+ turns until starvation. Fix: skip discovered non-M tiles from the suspected-guardian set (a confirmed D / U / . / feature tile is provably NOT a guardian). (2) Third trapped_no_d firing path: 600T on the current floor with no D found. Catches s=317 elf 3220T F1+F2 ping-pong (400 kills, kept revealing 1 new tile every 200T so neither the 200T-since-new nor 500T-since-new gates fired). 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 4.83 -> 5.14 (+6%), alive 2 -> 6 (3x), F1 deaths 16 -> 10 (-38%), F3 deaths 17 -> 16, F8+ runs 22 -> 23, F11 reached 1 -> 3, suspicious F<=3 count 26 -> 10 (-62%), loop_turns_total 13790 -> 11923. s=941 dwarf transformed: 2192T F1 wandering -> 2751T F7 killed by ELITE UNDEAD LICH. The death curve continues to flip from starvation to combat as the food/wedge gates close.",
    "Retreat-after-warp gate: +1 floor tolerance (build 332). User: 'Let's keep loop hunting.' Audit on the prior grid: 32 suspicious runs (turn >= 800 + floor <= 3) survived the trapped_no_d easing. Trace on s=99 elf (3893T on F3, 193 kills, 92.6% waste, no loop_turns flagged): T1192 warped F1 -> F2, fully explored F2 to 86% reach with D reachable by T1500, then the wayfinder routed onto a W tile at T1559 and force-warped back to F1. Root cause: retreat_to_floor flag fires when pc.z > max_z_via_stairs, and that threshold was strict-greater so a warp F1 -> F2 instantly triggered retreat mode. Retreat tiers strip D from priority ([U, V] only), so the agent never descends despite D being right there -- it instead routes toward W to ascend back. Eased: retreat now only fires when pc.z > max_z_via_stairs + 1 (a 2+ floor gap). Single-floor warps let the agent stay and descend D normally. 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 4.63 -> 4.83 (+4%), F3 deaths 25 -> 17 (-32%), F4-F7 each +2-3 runs, F11 (1) and F14 (1) reached for the first time, alive held at 2. s=99 elf went 3893T F3 -> 1444T F7 dying to a Wraith -- combat death at depth instead of wandering until starvation.",
    "trapped_no_d gate eased: catches stuck-but-not-quite-90% explorers (build 331). User screenshot of Eomer II (s=99 human, 1261T on F1, 52 kills, starved) prompted the 'high turn + low floor is suspicious' insight. Grid audit: 26 runs matched (turn >= 800 + max floor <= 2), most had loop_turns = 0 because they weren't 2-tile oscillations -- they were diffuse wandering across a small reachable region. s=88 dwarf F2: 28/32 reachable tiles visited (reach_pct = 85%), no new tile in 2000+ turns, BUT trapped_no_d required reach_pct >= 90 so the warp escape valve never fired -- agent burned 2500+ turns wandering until starvation. Eased the gate to two firing paths: (1) reach_pct >= 80% AND no new tile in 200T (was 90% / 200T), (2) no new tile in 500T regardless of reach_pct (covers rare case where reach_pct stays low because fog reveals add BFS-reachable tiles faster than the agent walks them). Mirrored the same in warp_mode. 5000-turn grid: avg max floor 4.15 -> 4.63 (+12%), F1 deaths 23 -> 16, F8+ runs 12 -> 22 (+83%), F9 reached 6 -> 11 (+83%), suspicious-runs 26 -> 14 (-46%), loop_turns_total 16775 -> 12230 (-27%). Agents now warp out of region-split wedges instead of wandering forever, hitting deeper hazards as intended.",
    "Final log + last actions now render on every run, not just deaths (build 330). User: 'Let's always capture the final log for all runs, not just the combat deaths.' Earlier the death_block + stuck_block rendered last-30-log + last-actions for not-alive and stuck runs only -- alive-at-turn-budget runs got no log tail. Added an else-branch that emits the same log + actions tables behind a green 'Survived to T{turn}. Run ended at the turn budget, not by death.' banner. New CSS class .alive-banner (green left-border, dim background) parallels the existing .death-banner (red) and .stuck-banner (amber) so the three end-states are visually distinct. 5000-turn grid sanity: 1/159 alive run (s=1500 human, F6 final) now shows its T4996 library-grimoire-search tail, matching the layout of the 158 death runs.",
    "Stair-wedge bounce eliminated: persistent-oscillation 'u' valve + wedge-floor descent block (build 329). User: 'Seems like there is still some starvation due to looping.' Audit on the 5000-turn carnage grid: 29/71 starvation deaths had mid-run loops averaging 612 turns wasted (vs 198 for combat deaths). Worst case s=88 human spent 1701 of 1862 turns in loops -- F2 was a region-split fragment with only U at (1,1) and a single '.' neighbour at (1,2), all other tiles walls. Agent bounced between them for the entire run while the food clock drained. Three coordinated fixes: (1) Persistent-oscillation streak counter on PlaytestSession (osc_streak) survives inventory pauses if the 1-tile pause is on the existing pair, so the streak doesn't reset every time the agent eats. (2) stairs_up_mode 'u' escape valve fires when osc_streak >= 50 -- ascend back to the prior floor when wedged on the current one. Build-318's symmetric valve was reverted because of descend/ascend cancellation; the 50-turn gate fixes that (descend-side fires immediately on stair-island, ascend-side only after a confirmed wedge). (3) PlaytestSession.wedge_floors set tracks every z escaped from via the 'u' valve. stairs_down_mode + game_loop wayfinder now both strip D from priority when current_z + 1 is a known wedge -- agent stays on the safe floor exploring for warps / Scroll of Descent instead of re-descending into the same trap. s=88 human loop_turns 1701 -> 241 (-86%). 5000-turn grid: alive 1 (held), starvation 71 -> 72, combat 67 -> 66 (within RNG noise); avg max floor 4.19 -> 4.15. The deeper fix is qualitative: the death curve no longer hides 1500-turn wedges inside what looked like starvation deaths.",
