    "Eat threshold 80 -> 50: less Ration waste in inventory mode (build 327). User pushed playtest to 5000 turns ('we want a lot of death and carnage'). The 5000-turn grid showed 159/159 dead, 102 starvation (64%), avg max floor 3.43. Audit of starvation deaths: agents restored 4-8 hunger/turn over their run (well above the 1/turn decay) yet spent 50-200 turns at hunger 0 -- they were binge-eating Rations at hunger 79, gaining only 21 of the 50-nut value because the hunger cap is 100. Inventory-mode eat trigger was `hunger < 80` while the game_loop open-inventory trigger was `hunger < 50`; aligned the two so each Ration delivers close to its full 50-nut payload. Modest impact: avg max floor 3.43 -> 3.54, F4 deaths 20 -> 28, F11 + F14 floors reached for the first time. Still 0% survival at 5000T. Deeper analysis shared with user: per-floor demand is ~140 nut, meat supply averages ~75 nut (55% drop rate × ~20 nut per piece × ~15 kills), so vendor floors stay surplus but vendor-less floors run a ~65 nut deficit -- two-three missed vendors compounds into starvation. Next levers under consideration: slow hunger decay, bump meat drop rate, bigger ration stacks.",
    "Player sprite picks race-filtered pool (build 326). User: 'The player sprites don't match the races outlined by the in game sprite picker.' app.py:5852 filters the character-creation picker by get_race_pool(race), but the seed-based auto-pick path in sprite_data.py:generate_player_sprite_html (and the playtest report's own copy of that logic) drew from the FULL _CHARACTERS_POOL -- so a dwarf hero could land on an elf-pool portrait, etc. Fixed both paths to filter by race first, then fall back to the full pool when a race has no curated picks. 159-seed grid sanity check: 159/159 reports now choose sprites from their race's curated subset. The (race, gender, name) seed continues to drive the deterministic pick within the filtered pool so the visual link between a report and a live launch of the same seed is preserved.",
